        public long usedStore()
        BytesAppData: The #of bytes in the allocated slots which are used by application data (including the record checksum). See BLZG-1551 : The data reported here used to be bad since #m_sizeDeletes could not being tracked correctly in the StorageStats because we do not know the actual #of bytes in the slot that contain application data when we finally recycle the slot. See BLZG-1646 BytesAppData counter can not be tracked accurately and should be removed
